title: Bourdieu's Art
abstract: "Bourdieu and Art" was a paper written for a graduate class in Art and Literature at York St. John University, York, England, in November 2010. It provides an overview of Bourdieu's work on the logic and symbolic power of the artistic world.

title: The New Zealand Class Structure
abstract: This article was written in 1985 as an introduction to the findings from the National Survey on Social Class in New Zealand, 1984. It provides a summary of findings of that survey, and it also offers an introduction to a book-length project 'Reinventing Capitalism' that is in preparation with Cambridge Scholars Press. The book is expected to be published early in 2019.
